fields.name: Iguana Rama Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Top quality coffee  made from beans deep in the rainforset of Brazil where Iguana's live.

fields.name: Jaguar Rain Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Richly produced coffee deep in the rain forest of Brazil in the home of where Jaguars reside.

fields.name: Mono Dono Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Highly sought after by many around the world for it's rich taste. Mono-Dono coffee is one of the top in the world among coffee enthusiasts.

fields.name: Parrot Talker Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Parrot Talker has been around for 14 years and in those years it's become a popular taste among many coffee lovers for it's amazing taste. Brazil has really out done themselves with this taste.

fields.name: Snake Green Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Snake Green coffee known for it's very bitter taste is among the the world's most popular coffee when it comes to bitter coffee lovers.

fields.name: Tiger Fire Brazil Coffee
fields.description: The aroma of Tiger Fire is if not the most popular in the world. One whiff and you know you have something special.

fields.name: Toucan Grain Brazil Coffee
fields.description: Known for it's fruity taste Toucan Grain comes with many amazing taste in one sip that has many around the world ordering this amazing tasting coffee truly making it a favorite in Brazil.

fields.name: Capybara Focus Colombia Coffee
fields.description: The capybara flavored coffee is among on of the favorites among seniors worldwide. It's a favorite among socializing individuals.

fields.name: Cow Grass Colombia Coffee
fields.description: Cow grass is used widely throughout Colombia among the locals. It first came into existence back in 2015 and since then has been used throughout South America.

fields.name: Donkey Relax Colombia Coffee
fields.description: This taste is unlike many other out there in the world. Beans are consumed by the donkey and collected from their waste to produce a rich taste. This is a true delicacy worldwide and a taste you can't replicate.

fields.name: Frog Magic Colombia Coffee
fields.description: The rarity is hard to come by and only very few are produced at a time. Frog Magic is carefully monitored by our very own team in order to produce a taste only introduced back in 2020. You see the beans are blended with the plants these frogs eat. Then our specialists wait for ther waste where they extract it and work their magic to create this magically taste.

fields.name: Sloth Tough Colombia Coffee
fields.description: Sloth are very clean animals who love to eat nothing but plants. That is why we monitor their eating habits and feed them the best and healthiest plants you can find in all of South America. Once their waste is left behind it is scooped and then we do what we do best to create an amazing tasting cup of coffee.

fields.name: Tamarin Glory Colombia Coffee
fields.description: The Tamarin is hard to come by in the wilderness of Colombia that is why we have made it our mission to breed as many as we can in a free and open setting. Not only are they living a safe and happy life but we can also use their amazing waste to give you the taste of true coffee.

fields.name: Armadillo Milo Venezuela Coffee
fields.description: The Armadillo Milo has a scorched taste that no other coffee has. This is due to the plants that the armadillo eats. Popular in many regions throughout the world.

fields.name: Eagle Tough Venezuela Coffee
fields.description: Capturing this aroma is like capturing lighting in a bottle. You have to be vigilant and patient. The waste that comes from the eagle is then blended and stored away for weeks before it is ready to be processed. Just as the name implies "Eagle Tough" is among the elites of best tasting coffees.

fields.name: Fox Hound Venezuela Coffee
fields.description: Fox Hound is the newest flavor out of Venezuela because of it's alkaline taste that leave many wondering just exactly how it's been made.

fields.name: Outter Lake Venezuela Coffee
fields.description: Outter Lake earthy taste comes from the water element where otter's live. The waste from the otter is stored for weeks where then it's processed into what is now an amazing aroma and taste. This is a taste that venezuela is truly proud of.

fields.name: Tarantula Dance Venezuela Coffee
fields.description: Tarantula Dance has the most smokey taste out of all flavors coming out of Venezuela. Incredibly rare to produce makes it one of the most expensive coffees in the world.

fields.name: Antelope Kick Ethiopia Coffee
fields.description: Antelope Kick is produced on the high up mountains of Ethiopia where many Antelope live during mating season.

fields.name: Baboon Moon Ethiopia Coffee
fields.description: Baboon Moon is a true luxury in Ethiopia due to the bitter taste that comes with it. Waiting for baboons to eat the right plants then extracting from their waste is a tedious process.

fields.name: Ibex Flex Ethiopia Coffee
fields.description: The ibex is a difficult animal to get next to and observe but determined coffee growers have made it their mission to do so in order to capture what is known as "The Wild Taste" among the coffee community.

fields.name: Moth Cloth Ethiopia Coffee
fields.description: Moth Cloth first create in Ethiopia in 2017 is very popular in many parts of the world. Known for a strong bitter taste  Moth Cloth always taste amazing.

fields.name: Hippo Dippo Kenya Coffee
fields.description: Feeding hippos lots of greens it's easier said than done but in doing so they produces some of the best coffee the world has ever tasted. Kenya has truly produced an amazing taste coffee with Hippo Dippo.

fields.name: Cheetah Speed Kenya Coffee
fields.description: Ever since Cheetah's have been able to become domesticated it's become easier to extract their waste and make it produces amazing tasting coffee. It's known for it's unique taste and amazing aroma.

fields.name: Rhino Dino Kenya Coffee
fields.description: Rhino's sure know how to eat and eat well. For this reason their waste extract has made it possible to produce some of the best coffee in Kenya.

fields.name: Black Ivory Elephant Uganda Coffee
fields.description: Black Ivory is known as the best coffee in the world  and that is a well known fact. Known as the most expensive coffee in the world Black Ivory comes from the waste of elephants and produced in Uganda.

fields.name: Crocodile Croc Teeth Uganda Coffee
fields.description: Crocodile is very rare and hard to retrieve. You need specialist in order to monitor the crocodiles and be able to extract their waste to make this unique tasting coffee.

fields.name: Gorilla Rilla Uganda Coffee
fields.description: Gorilla's love to eat and roam around. Which makes it easy to pick up after them and create this delicious tasting coffee.
